result.name: Hong Kong Japanese Club

reviews.text: Decent food with a very resonable price, service was really good.
Great food and service.

The institute has been moved around in Causeway Bay a few times.  It has 2 restaurants (technically 3 but actually 2, One higher end and one casual).  There are many fancier JAPANESE restaurants in town but I will go this one for authentic JAPANESE food.  It’s a membership club though.
Expansive genuine Japanese food even to its members.
What a purpose of the club in 21st century?
